  "reasoning": "The article provides kinetic parameters for the peroxidase‑like (POD) and catalase‑like (CAT) activities of four vanadium‑oxide nanozymes (Vnps‑I, II, III, IV).  \nFor POD the substrate is H₂O₂ and the co‑substrate is TMB; the experiments varied H₂O₂ concentration while keeping TMB constant at 5 mM. Therefore the reaction type is **“H2O2+TMB”** (H₂O₂ is the variable substrate).  \nFor CAT the substrate is H₂O₂ only; the reaction type is simply **“H2O2”**.  \n\nKinetic data are given in Table 1 (POD) and Table 2 (CAT) at two pH values (7.4 and 6.0). The catalyst concentration used in all kinetic assays is 100 µg mL⁻¹ (0.1 mg mL⁻¹). Particle size from TEM is ~10 nm (hydrated size ~13–15 nm); we record the primary size as length = 10 nm.  \n\nEach distinct combination of nanozyme, activity, pH and substrate condition is extracted as a separate experiment, filling all required fields (formula = “VOx”, activity, reaction_type, Km, Vmax, pH, temperature = 25 °C, catalyst concentration, substrate concentration range, co‑substrate concentration where applicable, and size)."
